Data Wragling - First Insights¶

2.1 - ScheduledDay & AppointmentDay names can be changed like "scheduled_day" & "appointment_day"¶

2.2 - All column names can be lower and there should be "_" instead of whitepace or "-" for better usage¶

2.3 - ScheduledDay & AppointmentDay seems to have redundant words like 'Z' and 'T', clear them & check if there is any other strings¶

2.4 - After deletion of strings in ScheduledDay & AppointmentDay check if they can convert to datetime objects to better usage¶

Solution --> It seems there are only 'Z' and 'T' exist (see below head & tail actions) .Delete only 'Z' & 'T' later on convert them to datatime , if there is no error this means there is no any other strings If there is an error find out the other string

2.5 - Non-Null & duplicate status should be checked¶

In [111]:
"""Below structure creates count & percentage of patients table seperately and then combines them for 4 spesific columns
   Thefore we can easily observe"""

"""I have added to percentage column in order to find out the data ratios of a spesified column
   Because, for example, when the time comes to compare diabetes & hipertension, compare them with only count could be deceptive
   There could be 6 value in hipertension 3 ill / 3 healty and 100 in diabetes 50 ill / 50 healthy --> percentages same, counts different"""

columns = ["hipertension", "diabetes", "alcoholism", "scholarship", "sms_received"]      
for i, column in enumerate(columns,1):
    a = df_no.groupby(column)["showed"].count()
    b = round(a.div(df_no[column].count())*100,1)
    c = pd.concat([a , b], axis=1, join='inner')
    c.columns=["showed_count", "showed_percentage"]
    print(c)

Question - 2.1 Are illnesses are really important ? Or which illness is more important ?¶

In [112]:
"""As I mentioned in data preparation section, to find out importance of illnesses (in that dataset) for going to an appointment
   illnesses column to be used.
   
   What i am looking for is that 
   
   1) percentage of people go to an appointment due to diabetes & hipertension & alcoholism (can be thought as sick / ill people)
   2) percentage of people going for an appointment due to reasons of check-up or something else without being sick 
   
   Therefore, in the graph below, 
   
   'Illness' part can be thought as percentage of people who suffer from diabetes or hipertension or alcoholism
   'Other' part can be considered as reasons like check-up / seasonal effect / location effect / sms effect etc which will be investigated in next chapters
   """
""" Below graph will depict us what is the main reason of going for an appointment """

a5 = df_no.groupby("illnesses")["showed"].count()
b5 = round(a5.div(df_no["illnesses"].count())*100,1)
b5.columns=["showed_percentage"]

ax = b5.plot(kind="bar", alpha = 0.9, color= "navy", figsize=(9,7.5))
ax.set_title("Showed Up Status - Illness", fontsize=15)
ax.set_xlabel("Illness Originated Or Other Reasons", fontsize=10)
ax.set_ylabel("Showed Patient Percentage", fontsize=10)
ax.set_ylim(0,100)

# create a list to collect the plt.patches data
totals = []

# find the values and append to list
for i in ax.patches:
    totals.append(i.get_height())

# set individual bar lables using above list
total = sum(totals)

# set individual bar lables using above list
for i in ax.patches:
    # get_x pulls left or right; get_height pushes up or down
    ax.text(i.get_x()+.15, i.get_height()-6, \
            str(round((i.get_height()/total)*100, 2))+'%', fontsize=16,
                color='white')

Limitations :What I have faced & the ways which I done to handle them !¶

1) The column names were difficult to use, they had capital letters, white spaces etc. Therefore I put lower cases & '_' instead of capital letters and whitespaces .

2) Schedule day and appointment day had unnecessray letters of 'Z' and 'T' which prevents the datetime usage schedule & appointment day. Therefore I have removed them and converted schedule and appointment day to datetime object.

3) No_Show column had 'Y' data which illustrates patients who did not show up to their appointment. They are not important for us. Therefore its better to delete no_show 'Y' in order not to create confusion

4)Data have not duplicates - it was clean - it was good for not to do additional cleaning process

5)Data have not any null item - again it was good for not to do additional preparing process

6)In column of 'Age', age of (-1) need to be defined cause it may be a wrong record. Its been included to calculations, because only 1 record can be neglectable considering 88208 rows.

7)I could not understand the column of "handcap" therefore I excluded it from the dataset. Its better to learn what it is

8)Data was sufficient for analysis but contains only 88208 occured appointments therefore it may be deceptive to use it for whole Brasil. From that reason, its better to have more & more data in order to predict whole Brasil's behaviour

9)There might be other factors except from SMS receive, types of illnesses etc. Therefore its better to have more columns which helps us to understand the behaviour. Maybe the there might some other types of illnesses which has a serious impact

Conclusion¶

In order to predict if a patient will show up to appointment, a patient's Location, Sex, Age, illness which patients suffer, SMS receive status, scholarship status and appointment month are important regarding to that dataset. Of course there might be any other contributers which have not been included to dataset.

For example, if a patient lives in Jardim Camburi, woman, age of 37, has a illness of hipertension, SMS received, included to welfare program and has an appointment day in May, most probably he / she will show up to appointment

You may find the main drivers of the every contributer below.

1) Location --> Jardim Camburi, Maria Ortiz, Resistencia Cities

2) Sex ---> Female

3) Age ---> Young people (Avg. Age : 37)

4) Month Of Appointment ---> May

5) Illnesses ---> Hypertension

6) SMS Receive ---> SMS Received (1) / (Y)

7) Scholarship ---> Have Scholarship (1) / (Y)
